					<description><![CDATA[<p>The leading global crypto exchange Binance has officially listed Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG) for spot trading. Both projects had their debuts on Binance Alpha, its early-stage listing platform,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/binance-lists-genius-terminal-genius-opengradient-opg/" data-wpel-link="internal">Binance List Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG) for Spot Trading</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The leading global crypto exchange Binance has </span><a href="https://www.binance.com/en/support/announcement/detail/4de6272354be421ba51ea042fd273a8d" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400;">officially listed</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG) for spot trading. </span>Both projects had their debuts on <a href="https://accounts.binance.com/register?ref=O0BTS35V" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer">Binance</a> Alpha, its early-stage listing platform, in April. The Binance GENIUS and OPG listing has already attracted strong market attention, as they are both fast-rising projects.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="2">Both tokens saw increased trading activity shortly after the announcement. This listing opens up fresh opportunities for spot traders looking to diversify their crypto portfolios.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="2">Here is everything users need to know about the Binance GENIUS and OPG listing, the trading pairs, and how to begin trading these new tokens. Also, Binance is hosting a campaign where new users who sign up with the Binance Referral Code O0BTS35 can earn $100 in USDT and 10% trading fee rebates.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><div class="b-cta-wrapper"><div class="b-cta b-cta--inline"><div class="b-cta__meta"><div class="user-score"></div><div class="promotion"></div></div><div class="b-cta__btn d-flex flex-column align-items-center justify-content-center"></div></div><!-- /.b-cta --></div></span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance Officially Lists GENIUS and OPG</span></h2>
<div id="attachment_201751" style="width: 1610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201751" class="size-full wp-image-201751" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/unnamed-5.jpg" alt="Binance Officially Lists GENIUS and OPG" width="1600" height="900" /><p id="caption-attachment-201751" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG)</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance opened spot trading for </span><a href="https://www.binance.com/en/my/wallet/exchange/deposit/crypto/GENIUS" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Genius Terminal (GENIUS)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><a href="https://www.binance.com/en/my/wallet/exchange/deposit/crypto/OPG" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400;">OpenGradient (OPG)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> on May 22, 2026. Trading support launched with several pairs across stablecoins and fiat markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Genius Terminal available trading pairs include:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">GENIUS/USDT</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">GENIUS/USDC</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">GENIUS/TRY</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The OpenGradient available trading pairs include:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">OPG/USDT</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">OPG/USDC</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">OPG/TRY</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Binance also confirmed that deposits opened before trading began. Withdrawals became available on May 23, 11:00 (UTC). Most importantly, GENIUS and OPG were listed with Seed Tags. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This means Binance considers them newer and potentially more volatile cryptocurrencies. Users must complete Binance’s risk awareness quiz before trading these tokens.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The listing time was briefly delayed by one hour. Binance later confirmed that trading started at 12:00 UTC instead of the original 11:00 UTC schedule.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Binance Events: </i></b><a href="https://chainplay.gg/blog/binance-alpha-solstice-airdrop-guide/https:/chainplay.gg/blog/binance-edge-trading-competition-guide/https:/chainplay.gg/blog/binance-alpha-gensyn-airdrop-guide/https:/chainplay.gg/blog/binance-46th-exclusive-tge-opengradient-guide/https:/chainplay.gg/blog/binance-alpha-genius-foundation-airdrop-guide/https:/chainplay.gg/blog/binance-soon-alpha-wave-2-airdrop-guide/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><b><i>Binance Alpha Solstice (SLX) Airdrop Goes Live on May 25</i></b></a></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">What Is Genius Terminal (GENIUS)?</span></h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_201750" style="width: 1441px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201750" class="size-full wp-image-201750" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/unnamed-6.jpg" alt="What Is Genius Terminal (GENIUS)?" width="1431" height="733" /><p id="caption-attachment-201750" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Genius Terminal</p></div>
<p><a href="https://chainplay.gg/blog/binance-alpha-genius-foundation-airdrop-guide/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Genius Terminal</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is a decentralized multi-chain trading terminal built for on-chain crypto trading. It combines spot trading, perpetual trading, and cross-chain execution into one interface. Genius Terminal aims to make decentralized trading feel as smooth as using a centralized exchange.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Genius Terminal focuses heavily on privacy and speed. One of its major features is a privacy layer called Gh0st. This system helps hide trading activity by splitting orders across wallets. The goal is to reduce tracking and front-running risks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The GENIUS token powers the ecosystem. It is used for governance, incentives, and network functions within the platform. The project reportedly has a maximum supply of 1 billion GENIUS tokens.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">What Is OpenGradient (OPG)?</span></h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_201749" style="width: 1210px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201749" class="size-full wp-image-201749" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/unnamed-7.jpg" alt="What Is OpenGradient (OPG)?" width="1200" height="630" /><p id="caption-attachment-201749" class="wp-caption-text">Source: OpenGradient (OPG)</p></div>
<p><a href="https://chainplay.gg/blog/binance-46th-exclusive-tge-opengradient-guide/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">OpenGradient</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is an AI-focused decentralized infrastructure network. The platform is designed to support AI model hosting, verification, and inference through decentralized GPU systems. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It allows developers and applications to outsource heavy AI workloads securely across distributed networks. The protocol uses Trusted Execution Environment (TET) nodes and decentralized computing clusters to process machine learning tasks. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">OpenGradient positions itself as a decentralized AI coprocessor for Web3 applications and autonomous AI agents. The OPG token powers payments, transaction fees, and validator operations within the network. OpenGradient also has a fixed supply of 1 billion tokens.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Binance Events: </i></b><a href="https://chainplay.gg/blog/binance-bsb-trading-competition-guide/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><b><i>Binance Block Street Network Trading Competition Guide</i></b></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">How Users Can Start Trading GENIUS and OPG</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you want to trade GENIUS or OPG on Binance, you first need a verified Binance account. After signing in, deposit USDT, USDC, or TRY into your Binance wallet. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_201748" style="width: 1021px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201748" class="size-full wp-image-201748" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/unnamed-8.jpg" alt="How Users Can Start Trading GENIUS and OPG" width="1011" height="606" /><p id="caption-attachment-201748" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG)</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Search for the GENIUS or OPG trading pairs on the Spot market.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201747" style="width: 1442px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201747" class="size-full wp-image-201747" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/unnamed-9.jpg" alt="How Users Can Start Trading GENIUS and OPG" width="1432" height="741" /><p id="caption-attachment-201747" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG)</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Traders should also complete Binance’s Seed Tag risk acknowledgment quiz before accessing the markets. Binance requires this for newer and higher-risk crypto assets.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_201746" style="width: 1042px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-201746" class="size-full wp-image-201746" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/unnamed-10.jpg" alt="How Users Can Start Trading GENIUS and OPG" width="1032" height="413" /><p id="caption-attachment-201746" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG)</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Users can place market orders for instant execution or limit orders to set their own preferred entry price. Because both assets are newly listed, price swings may remain high during the early trading period. Many new Binance listings often experience strong volatility within the first few days.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Binance Events: </i></b><a href="https://chainplay.gg/blog/binance-alpha-citrea-airdrop-guide/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><b><i>Binance Alpha Citrea (CTR) Airdrop Goes Live on May 26</i></b></a></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/binance-lists-genius-terminal-genius-opengradient-opg/" data-wpel-link="internal">Binance List Genius Terminal (GENIUS) and OpenGradient (OPG) for Spot Trading</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
